mmir: An R-package for Simple Biological Metric Calculations

10 Sequence Through Multiple Metrics

seq.df <- nest.df %>% 
  bind_cols(
    taxa_seq(.data = .,
             .key_col = unique_id,
             .counts_col = reporting_value,
             .filter_cols_vec = c("class", "order", "family"),
             .group_col = genus,
             .job = "rich",
             .unnest_col = data))
nest.df <- nest.df %>% 
  bind_cols(
    taxa_seq(.data = .,
             .key_col = unique_id,
             .counts_col = reporting_value,
             .filter_cols_vec = c("class", "order", "family"),
             .group_col = genus,
             .job = "rich"),
    taxa_seq(.data = .,
             .key_col = unique_id,
             .counts_col = reporting_value,
             .filter_cols_vec = c("class", "order", "family"),
             .group_col = genus,
             .job = "pct"),
    taxa_seq(.data = .,
             .key_col = unique_id,
             .counts_col = reporting_value,
             .filter_cols_vec = c("class", "order", "family"),
             .group_col = genus,
             .base_log = 2,
             .job = "shannon"))
